Resolve stale ContainerEngine::Auto in pod hosts

Pods stored by pre-Podman rumpelpod versions (0.2/0.3, and any version
before per-pod container-engine tracking existed) carry
`ContainerEngine::Auto` in the database forever: a fresh launch
resolves `Auto` to a concrete engine before storing the host, but
nothing re-resolved a `Host` loaded back from storage before it was
used to reconnect, stop, delete, or fork an existing pod.

`restore_running_pods`, which runs unconditionally on daemon startup
to reconnect to pods that were running before a restart, hit this via
`Executor::new`'s `panic!("... unresolved container engine auto")`,
crash-looping the whole daemon (rumpelpod.service repeatedly restarting
in systemd).

Resolve the engine at `HostConnectionRegistry::get_or_create`/`get`,
the single chokepoint through which every Docker/SSH connection is
built, and also right after loading a stored host in the `rumpel
enter` reentry and fork paths so the `LaunchResult` handed back to
clients never carries `Auto` either. Kubernetes hosts are left
untouched: their `image_builder` engine is irrelevant to opening a
connection to an already-running cluster pod.

Added a regression test that rewrites a pod's stored host to the
legacy bare-string `"Localhost"` format and restarts the daemon.
